ch class to play!  I am now debating a ranger, as I've never played one before.  <br><br>Might someone provide some insight into which classes are needed on this server?  Which classes are over-used (for instance Druids run rampant on my old server) on this server?  I really want to create a character I know I will stick with.  I am unsure what to do.<br><br>Thanks for any advice.<br><br>Undecided Adventurer<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 10:00:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New to FV, Help Requested Please!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=1735.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...1735.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=1726.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...1726.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=1673.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...1673.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=1685.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...1685.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>There are a few threads already around debating the topic. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>My advice would be to worry less about what is or isn't common, and focus on what you will enjoy playing. Folks on FV tend to be a bit more likely to make do with unorthodox groups instead of insisting on specific characters. They also tend to be a bit more self-reliant than other servers, from what I have seen (translate that to mean you will probably solo more). If you like to or need to group alot, you will probably want to be in a guild.<br><br>Also, your alignment and guild and race will affect what seems common or rare here. There may be a reasonable number of necromancers (or not - much debated), but there is certainly a shortage of necros in good-aligned guilds, for example. There are guilds with plenty of clerics, and there are guilds with almost none. Because everyone doesn't have easy access to twinks and alts, every guild isn't fully stocked with &quot;my main is a warrior, but I have a wizzie twink for ports and an enchanter twink for trades&quot; people.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Gnome Mageling <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=larneysilversmith>Larney Silversmith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/16/02 2:23:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> New Character Decisions</span><hr size=1> One of the first characters I ever played (and stuck with) was a magician. The magician class is alot of fun in that you can solo as well as be an effective part of a group. It is also great for this server in that you will eventually be able to summon everthing you need. (I think I spent the first 10 levels with just a robe because I was worried I wouldn't find my corpse). This is of great help on a server where money is hard to come across in the beginning. Additionally, on this server there are many true newbies who are drawn by that roleplay tag on the server listing. Also many people are &quot;untwinked&quot; since we have only one character each. Therefore, you can summon items that people will actually find helpful such as magic swords, spears, and armor. Having high intelligence will also leave you open to a successful career in several tradeskills, since on Firiona Vie the untwinked people actually have need of things like banded armor. Another good reason is that magicians have the best pets, making pelt and silk collecting extremely easy. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.gamelinx.com/silversmith/images/ls_logo.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elytaofthepride>Elyta of the Pride</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/17/02 11:32:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Character Decisions</span><hr size=1> Be a Gnome hon,  and you cant go far wrong!!<br><br>Everyone here just wishes they had been born a gnome. Ak'Anon is the finest city in Norath, Gnomes are the best and most helpful group of people.... what more do I need to say?<br><br>hehehehehe<br><br>Elyta<br>Member of the Tinker's Pride <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showNextMessage?topicID=42.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=42.topic&index=